ducted under the terms of the Third Reform Act through to the 1997 referenda in favour of devolved assemblies in Scotland and Wales. This was the period in which British politicians most obviously addressed a mass, British-wide electorate, seeking national approval for policies and programmes to be enacted on a UK-wide basis. Aimed at scholars and students of modern British history this volume will also interest the general reader who wishes to get to grips with some of the latest thinking about British politics.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 7aHISTORY / Europe / Great Britain / General.2bisacsh  aDuncan Tanner.  aGovernance.  aGovernment.  aModern Britain.  aModern Wales.  aPolitics.1 aClarke, Peter, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCragoe, Matthew, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDavis, John, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEdwards, Andrew, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEdwards, Andrew, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aFielding, Steven, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHowell, David, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLawrence, Jon, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aThane, Pat, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aThorpe, Andrew, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWiliam, Mari Elin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWilliams, Chris, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWilliams, Chris, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManchester Univ